<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>HTML Code Viewer</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Ideal structure of an HTML page!</h1>
    <pre>
        &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
        &lt;html lang="en"&gt;
        &lt;head&gt;
            &lt;meta charset="UTF-8" /&gt;
            &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" /&gt;
            &lt;meta name="description" content="A brief description of your website." /&gt;
            &lt;title&gt;Your Website Title&lt;/title&gt;
        
            &lt;!-- Link to external CSS --&gt;
            &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css" /&gt;
        
            &lt;!-- Optional: Favicon --&gt;
            &lt;link rel="icon" href="images/favicon.ico" type="image/x-icon" /&gt;
        &lt;/head&gt;
        &lt;body&gt;
            &lt;!-- Header --&gt;
            &lt;header&gt;
            &lt;h1&gt;Welcome to My Website&lt;/h1&gt;
            &lt;nav&gt;
                &lt;ul&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="index.html" class="active"&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="about.html"&gt;About&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;!-- Add more links --&gt;
                &lt;/ul&gt;
            &lt;/nav&gt;
            &lt;/header&gt;
        
            &lt;!-- Main content --&gt;
            &lt;main&gt;
            &lt;section&gt;
                &lt;h2&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;This is the main content of your homepage.&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;/section&gt;
            &lt;!-- Add more sections as needed --&gt;
            &lt;/main&gt;
        
            &lt;!-- Footer --&gt;
            &lt;footer&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;&amp;copy; 2025 Your Name. All rights reserved.&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;/footer&gt;
        
            &lt;!-- Link to JavaScript --&gt;
            &lt;script src="js/main.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
        &lt;/body&gt;
        &lt;/html&gt;
    </pre>
<hr><hr><hr>



<!-- Ideal Sturctre of an HTML path! -->
    <pre>
        <h1>Ideal Sturctre of an HTML path!</h1>
        project-name/
        ├── index.html              # Main HTML file
        ├── about.html              # Additional HTML page (example)
        ├── css/                    # Stylesheets
        │   └── style.css
        ├── js/                     # JavaScript files
        │   └── main.js
        ├── images/                 # Image assets
        │   └── logo.png
        ├── fonts/                  # Custom fonts (optional)
        │   └── roboto.woff
        ├── assets/                 # Other assets like videos, docs (optional)
        │   └── intro.mp4
        ├── components/             # Reusable HTML parts (optional)
        │   └── header.html
        └── README.md               # Documentation (optional)

    </pre>
<hr>




<pre><p>
    <b><big>Basics about the HTML</big></b>
        If we want to print your HTML code as visible text on the webpage (instead of having the browser 
        interpret and render it), you need to escape special characters like &lt, &gt, and &. The easiest way
        to do this is by placing your code inside a &lt pre &gt and &lt code &gt block and replacing special characters
        with HTML entities.

        To show HTML code as-is on the page, you need to escape it using HTML entities:

        &lt → & lt;

        &gt → & gt;

        &amp → & amp;
        Note: no spaces between & and lt/gt/amp </p>
    </pre>

</body>
</html>

